# Heading 1

## R Markdown

### <!--This is a comment  -->Heading 3

This is an R Markdown document. Markdown is a simple formatting syntax for authoring HTML, PDF, and MS Word documents. For more details on using R Markdown see <http://rmarkdown.rstudio.com>.

1.  When you click the ***Knit*** button a document will be generated that includes both content as well as the output of any embedded R code chunks within the document. You can embed an R code chunk like this:

| Outcome | Col2 | Col3 |
|---------|------|------|
| SCR     |      |      |
| Ratings |      |      |
|         |      |      |

```{r cars, include = TRUE}
summary(cars)
```

## Including Plots

You can also embed plots, for example: The mean is M = `r mean(cars$speed)`.

```{r pressure, include = TRUE}
plot(pressure)
```

Note that the `echo = FALSE` parameter was added to the code chunk to prevent printing of the R code that generated the plot.
